'''Rodrigo Javier De Paul'''  ({{IPA|es|roˈðɾiɣo ðe pol}};<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 June 2023 |title=Rodrigo De Paul en Llave a la Eternidad |trans-title=Rodrigo De Paul in Key to Eternity |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e5K_uGlSitE&t=238s |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=Televisión Pública |language=es |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814151840/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e5K_uGlSitE&t=238s |url-status=live }}</ref> born 24 May 1994) is an Argentine professional football player who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Inter Miami]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

He made his senior international debut in 2018 and has won the [[2021 Copa América]], [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], and [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==
===Racing Club===
Born in [[Sarandí, Buenos Aires|Sarandí]], [[Greater Buenos Aires]], De Paul joined [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]'s youth setup in 2002, aged eight.<ref>[http://www.deportevalenciano.com/2014/05/02/as%C3%AD-es-rodrigo-de-paul-nuevo-jugador-del-valencia-cf Así es Rodrigo de Paul, nuevo jugador del Valencia CF (This is Rodrigo de Paul, new player of Valencia CF)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811205336/http://www.deportevalenciano.com/2014/05/02/as%C3%AD-es-rodrigo-de-paul-nuevo-jugador-del-valencia-cf |date=11 August 2014 }}; Deporte Valenciano, 2 May 2014 {{in lang|es}}</ref> He was called up to the main squad on 24 June 2012, while still a junior, for a match against [[Club Atlético Vélez Sarsfield|Vélez Sarsfield]], but remained unused in the 1–2 home loss.

On 10 February 2013, De Paul played his first match as a professional, [[Substitute (association football)|replacing]] [[Mauro Camoranesi]] in the 86th minute of a 0–3 loss at [[Atlético de Rafaela]].<ref>[http://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/en-su-casa-atletico-de-rafaela-goleo-racing En su casa, Atlético de Rafaela goleó a Racing (At home, Atlético de Rafaela thrashed Racing)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810050055/http://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/en-su-casa-atletico-de-rafaela-goleo-racing |date=10 August 2014 }}; Mundo D, 10 February 2013 {{in lang|es}}</ref> He scored his first goal a month later, netting the last through a long-range shot in a 3–0 win at [[San Martín de San Juan]].<ref>[http://canchallena.lanacion.com.ar/1561653-san-martin-racing-un-encuentro-rodeado-de-pensamientos-maliciosos En otro partido con incidentes, Racing goleó y ayudó a Independiente (In another match with incidents, Racing thrashed and helped Independiente)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208153344/http://canchallena.lanacion.com.ar/1561653-san-martin-racing-un-encuentro-rodeado-de-pensamientos-maliciosos |date=8 December 2015 }}; Cancha Llena, 10 March 2013 {{in lang|es}}</ref>

De Paul appeared in 19 matches during the [[2012–13 Argentine Primera División season|2012–13 campaign]]. He then played a key part in [[2013–14 Argentine Primera División season|2013–14]], featuring in 35 matches and scoring four times.

===Valencia===
[[File:Audi quattro-Cup (11-07-2015) 34 (Rodrigo De Paul cropped).JPG|upright|thumb|left|De Paul with [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in 2015]]
On 9 May 2014, it was announced that [[Valencia CF]] agreed to a US$6.5 million deal for De Paul with Racing.<ref>[http://www.valenciacf.com/ver/35926/comunicado-oficial.html Comunicado Oficial (Official announcement)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221113104506/https://www.valenciacf.com/ver/35926/comunicado-oficial.html |date=13 November 2022 }}; Valencia's official website, 9 May 2014 {{in lang|es}}</ref> He signed a five-year deal with ''Los Che'' on 6 June,<ref>[http://www.valenciacf.com/ver/36138/benvingutdepaul---rodrigo-de-paul--nuevo-jugador-del-valencia-cf.html Rodrigo de Paul, nuevo jugador del Valencia CF (Rodrigo de Paul, new player of Valencia CF)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221130143203/https://www.valenciacf.com/ver/36138/benvingutdepaul---rodrigo-de-paul--nuevo-jugador-del-valencia-cf.html |date=30 November 2022 }}; Valencia's official website, 6 June 2014 {{in lang|es}}</ref> and made his [[La Liga]] debut on 23 August under head coach [[Nuno Espírito Santo]], replacing [[Paco Alcácer]] in the 65th minute in a 1–1 away draw against [[Sevilla FC]], but being [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] just one minute later due to fouling [[Aleix Vidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/primera/jornada_1/sev_val/|title=Punto de fe del Valencia|trans-title=Valencia point of faith|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=23 August 2014|access-date=3 September 2014|archive-date=16 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210616180028/https://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/primera/jornada_1/sev_val/|url-status=live}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for the club on 4 December 2014 in the 2–1 win against [[Rayo Vallecano]] in the [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/ath-bilbao-vs-valencia/322437|title=Copa del Rey: Rodrigo de Paul gives Valencia 2-1 advantage over Rayo|publisher=ESPN|language=en|date=4 December 2014|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=8 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220608091343/https://www.skysports.com/football/ath-bilbao-vs-valencia/322437|url-status=live}}</ref> He followed this up with his first La Liga goal on 9 April 2015 against [[Athletic Bilbao]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/ath-bilbao-vs-valencia/322437|title=Athletic Bilbao 1 Valencia 1|publisher=Sports Mole|language=en|date=9 April 2015|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=8 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220608091343/https://www.skysports.com/football/ath-bilbao-vs-valencia/322437|url-status=live}}</ref> making 29 appearances in all competitions during his first season at the club.

After making 14 appearances in all competitions during the first half of the 2015–16 season, including two in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]. On 4 February 2016, he was loaned out by then Valencia manager [[Gary Neville]] to his former side [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/valencia/transfer-talk/news/valencia-youngster-joins-racing-on-loan_265563.html|title=Valencia youngster Rodrigo de Paul joins Racing Club on loan|publisher=Sports Mole|language=en|date=4 February 2016|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=3 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220603042701/https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/valencia/transfer-talk/news/valencia-youngster-joins-racing-on-loan_265563.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first and only goal in a victory against Bolívar on 24 February in the [[Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/racing-open-group-stage-campaign-with-comfy-bolivar-win|title=RACING OPEN GROUP STAGE CAMPAIGN WITH COMFY BOLIVAR WIN|work=Fox Sports|language=en|date=25 February 2016|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=8 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220608091343/https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/racing-open-group-stage-campaign-with-comfy-bolivar-win|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Udinese===
On 20 July 2016, De Paul was transferred to Italian [[Serie A]] club [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.valenciacf.com/ver/59684/comunicado-oficial--traspaso-de-rodrigo-de-paul.html|title=VCF Official Statement {{!}} Rodrigo de Paul transferred to Udinese|publisher=Valencia CF|date=20 July 2016|access-date=21 July 2016|archive-date=10 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220110084653/http://en.valenciacf.com/ver/59684/comunicado-oficial--traspaso-de-rodrigo-de-paul.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut on 20 August 2016 against [[AS Roma]] in a 4–0 defeat. He scored his first goal for the club on 29 January 2017 against [[AC Milan]] in a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/match/udinese-v-milan/report/1gd1syr5vv2dqh5xvgbamnjl5|title=Udinese 2 AC Milan 1|publisher=Goal.com|language=en|date=29 January 2017|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=18 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210818094016/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/match/udinese-v-milan/report/1gd1syr5vv2dqh5xvgbamnjl5|url-status=live}}</ref>

He started the [[2018–19 Udinese Calcio season|2018–19]] season with four goals in the first six matches of the Serie A season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/english/sports/udinese-claims-2-0-win-over-last-placed-chievo-in-serie-a/50000266-3758643|title=Udinese claims 2–0 win over last-placed Chievo in Serie A|newspaper=www.efe.com|publisher=Efe|language=en|date=23 September 2018|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=18 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210818094017/https://www.efe.com/efe/english/sports/udinese-claims-2-0-win-over-last-placed-chievo-in-serie-a/50000266-3758643|url-status=live}}</ref> He would finish the season as Udinese top goal scorer with nine goals during the [[2018–19 Udinese Calcio season]] and also nine assists.<ref name="Football Italia">{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/145277/official-de-paul-extends-udinese|title=Official: De Paul extends at Udinese|publisher=Football Italia|language=en|date=29 January 2017|access-date=1 September 2020|archive-date=25 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125075842/https://www.football-italia.net/145277/official-de-paul-extends-udinese|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 15 October 2019, De Paul signed a new five-year contract at Udinese.<ref name="Football Italia"/> He would score seven goals and gain six assists for Udinese in Serie A during the 2019–20 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/156821/report-udinese-want-%E2%82%AC40m-de-paul|title=Report: Udinese want €40m for De Paul|publisher=Football Italia|language=en|date=5 August 2020|access-date=1 September 2020|archive-date=18 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918002246/https://www.football-italia.net/156821/report-udinese-want-%E2%82%AC40m-de-paul|url-status=live}}</ref>

De Paul became Udinese's [[Captain (association football)|club captain]] in December 2020, replacing [[Kevin Lasagna]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tuttoudinese.it/notizie/lasagna-declassato-nonostante-la-sua-titolarita-ieri-il-capitano-era-de-paul-79609 |title=Lasagna "declassato"? Nonostante la sua titolarità ieri il capitano era De Paul |website=tuttoudinese.it |publisher=Tutto Udinese |date=24 December 2020 |access-date=6 February 2021 |language=it |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128192405/https://www.tuttoudinese.it/notizie/lasagna-declassato-nonostante-la-sua-titolarita-ieri-il-capitano-era-de-paul-79609 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
[[File:Rodrigo de Paul in 2022.jpeg|thumb|upright=0.6|De Paul playing for [[Atlético Madrid]] in 2022]]
On 12 July 2021, De Paul signed a five-year contract with [[Atlético Madrid]]. He joined his new club just days after winning the [[2021 Copa América|Copa América]] with Argentina.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Club Atlético de Madrid - Welcome, Rodrigo de Paul!|url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-rodrigo-de-paul|access-date=12 July 2021|website=Club Atlético de Madrid|language=en|archive-date=22 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122210315/https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-rodrigo-de-paul|url-status=live}}</ref> On 7 December 2021, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 away win against [[FC Porto]] in the final group game of the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/atleti-win-at-porto-to-qualify-for-ucl-last-16 |title=Atleti win at Porto to qualify for UCL last 16 |publisher=Atlético Madrid |date=7 December 2021 }}</ref>

===Inter Miami===
On 25 July 2025, De Paul joined Major League Soccer club [[Inter Miami CF|Inter Miami]] on an initial six-month loan from [[Atlético Madrid]], with a mandatory purchase clause worth €15 million plus potential bonuses. He is expected to sign a four-year deal through 2029 once the move becomes permanent.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rodrigo De Paul Joins Inter Miami |url=https://www.transferwatcher.com/mls-transfers/rodrigo-de-paul-joins-inter-miami |website=Transferwatcher.com |date=26 July 2025 |access-date=26 July 2025}}</ref> A month later, on 6 August, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 win over [[Club Universidad Nacional|Pumas UNAM]] during the [[2025 Leagues Cup league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/rodrigo-de-paul-combines-with-luis-suarez-for-first-inter-miami-goal |title=Rodrigo De Paul comes up clutch with first Inter Miami goal |publisher=MLSsoccer.com |date=7 August 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Rodrigo de Paul (2022).jpg|thumb|upright|left|De Paul playing for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
De Paul made his senior international debut for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in a 4–0 victory against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] on 11 October 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/iraq-vs-argentina/402273|title=Iraq 0 Argentina 4|publisher=Sky Sports|language=en|date=11 October 2018|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=8 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221108044829/https://www.skysports.com/football/iraq-vs-argentina/402273|url-status=live}}</ref> and later became a regular under manager [[Lionel Scaloni]]; he was part of the Argentina squad that finished third in the [[Copa América 2019]] after beating [[Chile national football team|Chile]] 2–1 in the third-place match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://copaamerica.com/es/noticias/Argentina-vencio-2-1-a-Chile-y-se-quedo-con-el-tercer-puesto/|title=Argentina venció 2-1 a Chile y se quedó con el tercer puesto|publisher=CONMEBOL|language=es|date=6 July 2019|access-date=20 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708015400/https://copaamerica.com/es/noticias/argentina-vencio-2-1-a-chile-y-se-quedo-con-el-tercer-puesto/|archive-date=8 July 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 3 July 2021, De Paul scored the opening goal in a 3–0 win over [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] in the quarter-finals of the [[2021 Copa América]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/argentina-beat-ecuador-3-0-move-into-copa-america-semi-2021-07-04/ |title=Argentina beat Ecuador 3-0 to move into Copa America semi |work=Reuters |date=4 July 2021 |access-date=11 July 2021 |archive-date=6 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221206141833/https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/argentina-beat-ecuador-3-0-move-into-copa-america-semi-2021-07-04/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[2021 Copa América Final|final]] of the tournament against the hosts [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], De Paul's long pass set up [[Ángel Di María]] to score the only goal of the match, allowing Argentina to capture their joint record 15th Copa América title and their first major international title since [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2008]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/brazil-argentina-live-score-updates-highlights-copa-america-final/1tfk0vd23j2gj1a70vsyw2emub|title=Highlights of Copa America final 2021|access-date=11 July 2021|archive-date=29 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129024727/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/brazil-argentina-live-score-updates-highlights-copa-america-final/1tfk0vd23j2gj1a70vsyw2emub|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Copa América final">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jul/10/argentina-v-brazil-copa-america-final-live |title=Argentina 1-0 Brazil: Copa América final – live! |work=The Guardian |last1=Graham |first1=Bryan Armen |date=11 July 2021 |access-date=11 July 2021 |archive-date=12 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712135151/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jul/10/argentina-v-brazil-copa-america-final-live |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 10 October 2021, De Paul scored a goal in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)#Matchday 5|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)]], in a 3–0 win over [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Argentina 3-0 Uruguay (11 Oct, 2021) Game Analysis - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/561078 |access-date=2025-12-17 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> 

He was also part of the squad that won the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Pope |first1=Greg LeaContributions from Conor |last2=Hancock |first2=Tom |last3=Mazur |first3=Martin |last4=published |first4=Alasdair Mackenzie |date=2022-12-18 |title=Argentina World Cup 2022 squad: Lionel Scaloni's full team |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/argentina-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar |access-date=2023-03-03 |website=fourfourtwo.com |language=en |archive-date=18 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221218133642/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/argentina-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=15 June 2024 |title=Lionel Scaloni dio a conocer la lista de la Selección argentina para la Copa América 2024 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/futbol/2024/06/15/lionel-scaloni-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-la-seleccion-argentina-para-la-copa-america-2024/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwqf20BhBwEiwAt7dtdeK13_I24H4iqEBua7UtmDLn6_x-FfDm-gzEseLS8vJCnOlmjC3PlBoCHEwQAvD_BwE |access-date=23 July 2024 |work=[[Todo Noticias]]}}</ref>
{{clear}}

== Personal life ==
[[File:25th Laureus World Sports Awards - Red Carpet - Rodrigo de Paul - 240422 192702 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|De Paul at the [[Laureus World Sports Awards]] in 2024]]
Rodrigo's mother Mónica Ferraroti is of [[Italian descent]], which earned him [[Italian citizenship]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mosca |first=Lorenzo |date=2021-07-12 |title=De Paul, addio Udinese. All'Atletico Madrid dell'argentino Simeone per 35 milioni |url=https://www.gauchonews.it/calcio-argentino-sport/rodrigo-de-paul-udinese-venduto-atletico-madrid/ |access-date=2022-12-19 |website=Gaucho News |language=it-IT |archive-date=19 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221219084959/https://www.gauchonews.it/calcio-argentino-sport/rodrigo-de-paul-udinese-venduto-atletico-madrid/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Redazione |date=2017-02-18 |title=Italia, oriundi-mania: ecco la top 11 dei "convocabili" |url=http://radiogoal24.it/2017/02/18/italia-oriundi-mania-ecco-la-top-11-dei-convocabili/ |access-date=2022-12-19 |website=RadioGoal24 |language=it-IT |archive-date=19 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221219084958/http://radiogoal24.it/2017/02/18/italia-oriundi-mania-ecco-la-top-11-dei-convocabili/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She worked as the [[treasurer]] of the local football club Deportivo Belgrano de Sarandí, which De Paul joined at the age of three. After the divorce of his parents, De Paul was raised by his paternal grandfather Osvaldo De Paul, whom he acknowledges as the key influence on his upbringing.<ref>{{cite news |last=Viera |first=Luana |title=Rodrigo De Paul, del barrio al mundo: el asado que sorprendió a sus amigos de Sarandí, una mamá también papá y el abuelo que lleva tatuado |work=Todo Noticias |date=3 March 2022 |accessdate=12 January 2026 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/seleccion-argentina/2021/11/28/rodrigo-de-paul-del-barrio-al-mundo-el-asado-que-sorprendio-a-sus-amigos-de-sarandi-una-mama-tambien-papa-y-el-abuelo-que-lleva-tatuado/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211128135911/https://tn.com.ar/deportes/seleccion-argentina/2021/11/28/rodrigo-de-paul-del-barrio-al-mundo-el-asado-que-sorprendio-a-sus-amigos-de-sarandi-una-mama-tambien-papa-y-el-abuelo-que-lleva-tatuado/ |archive-date=28 November 2021 |url-status=live |lang=es}}</ref>

De Paul was in a relationship with Argentine model Camila Homs for twelve years. They have two children together. In January 2022, the couple confirmed that they were separating.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|date=2022-02-18|title=Rodrigo De Paul y Camila Homs: Cómo la historia de un amor terminó en un escándalo internacional|url=https://www.prensalibre.com/vida/escenario/rodrigo-de-paul-y-camila-homs-la-historia-de-un-amor-que-termino-en-un-escandalo-internacional/|access-date=2022-12-19|website=www.prensalibre.com|language=es-SP|archive-date=23 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230123115116/https://www.prensalibre.com/vida/escenario/rodrigo-de-paul-y-camila-homs-la-historia-de-un-amor-que-termino-en-un-escandalo-internacional/|url-status=live}}</ref> De Paul dated Argentine singer [[Tini (singer)|Tini]] from August 2021 to August 2023 and again since 2025.<ref>* {{Cite magazine|url=https://caras.perfil.com/noticias/celebridades/rodrigo-de-paul-le-confeso-su-amor-a-tini-stoessel-te-amo.phtml|title=Rodrigo De Paul le confesó su amor a Tini Stoessel: "Te amo"|magazine=[[Caras (magazine)|Caras]]|date=20 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220825213006/https://caras.perfil.com/noticias/celebridades/rodrigo-de-paul-le-confeso-su-amor-a-tini-stoessel-te-amo.phtml|archive-date=25 August 2022|access-date=25 August 2022|language=es|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite news |last=Sánchez |first=Miguel Jorge |date=2 August 2023 |title=Rodrigo de Paul y Tini Stoessel confirman su separación: "Vivimos momentos muy lindos" |work=[[La Vanguardia]] |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/gente/20230802/9147311/rodrigo-paul-tini-stoessel-confirman-separacion-vivimos-momentos-lindos.html |access-date=2 August 2023 |archive-date=2 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230802075608/https://www.lavanguardia.com/gente/20230802/9147311/rodrigo-paul-tini-stoessel-confirman-separacion-vivimos-momentos-lindos.html |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite news |date=2 August 2023 |title=Tini Stoessel y Rodrigo De Paul anunciaron su separación: "Vivimos momentos muy lindos" |work=[[La Nación]] |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/tini-stoessel-y-rodrigo-de-paul-anunciaron-su-separacion-vivimos-momentos-muy-lindos-nid01082023/ |access-date=2 August 2023 |archive-date=1 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230801230657/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/espectaculos/tini-stoessel-y-rodrigo-de-paul-anunciaron-su-separacion-vivimos-momentos-muy-lindos-nid01082023/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

